eu.trentorise.smartcampus.osm.android.views.overlay

Class ItemizedOverlay<Item extends OverlayItem>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.trentorise.smartcampus.osm.android.views.overlay.Overlay
      • eu.trentorise.smartcampus.osm.android.views.overlay.SafeDrawOverlay
        • eu.trentorise.smartcampus.osm.android.views.overlay.ItemizedOverlay<Item>
  • Type Parameters:
    Item -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Overlay.Snappable, OverlayConstants
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ItemizedIconOverlay

    public abstract class ItemizedOverlay<Item extends OverlayItem>
extends SafeDrawOverlay
implements Overlay.Snappable
    Draws a list of OverlayItem as markers to a map. The item with the lowest index is drawn as last and therefore the 'topmost' marker. It also gets checked for onTap first. This class is generic, because you then you get your custom item-class passed back in onTap().
    Author:
    Marc Kurtz, Nicolas Gramlich, Theodore Hong, Fred Eisele

      • setFocus

        public void setFocus(Item item)
        If the given Item is found in the overlay, force it to be the current focus-bearer. Any registered ItemizedOverlay#OnFocusChangeListener will be notified. This does not move the map, so if the Item isn't already centered, the user may get confused. If the Item is not found, this is a no-op. You can also pass null to remove focus.

      • getFocus
